67.1	John_Henry_(folklore)	John Henry (folklore)	John Henry is an American folk hero and tall tale. Henry worked as a "steel-driver"â€”a man tasked with hammering and chiseling rock in the construction of tunnels for railroad tracks. In the legend, John Henry's prowess as a steel-driver was measured in a race against a steam powered hammer, which he won only to die in victory with his hammer in his hand. The story of John Henry has been the subject of numerous songs, stories, plays, and novels.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/John_Henry-27527.jpg/250px-John_Henry-27527.jpg
